  "texts": [
    "LLMs operate on graphs encoded as sequences of tokens S(G, ℓ):= (s 1,..., s Qgraph).",
    "They take as input both this and a task description T:= (t 1,..., t Qtask) to generates answer f LLM (T, S(G, ℓ)):= (y 1,..., y A).",
    "The answer tokens are iteratively sampled or greedily chosen from the autoregressive distribution defined by the LLM parameters.",
    "Importantly, LLMs are not permutation invariant by design.",
    "Distinct labelings ℓ and serializations S of the same graph yield distinct input strings for which LLMs may yield distinct outputs."
  ],
  "correct_citations": []
}